  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-Sectoral Response to Acute Humanitarian Needs of Flood-Affected Population and Those At-Risk of Disease Outbreak in Bentiu IDP Camp</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the time critical needs highlighted in the South Sudan Humanitarian Fund First Reserve Allocation - Strategy Paper, IOM is implementing a multi-sectoral and life-saving response to the acute humanitarian needs of people displaced due to conflict in Tambura County and flooding in targeted locations, as well as internally displaced persons (IDPs) in Bentiu Camp at risk of disease outbreak, particularly Hepatitis E. This project is leveraging IOM&#x2019;s existing presence in Bentiu IDP Camp, as well as its role as Camp Manager and active participation in all relevant coordination forums, whilst also capitalizing upon the capacity of the Organization to rapidly mobilize shelter/non-food item (S-NFI) teams in hard-to-reach locations. Finally, the S-NFI and water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) Pipelines will enable IOM to efficiently support lifesaving frontline responses, by ensuring the reliable, cost-effective and steady stream of core relief supplies to partners for distribution to crisis-affected populations in Bentiu IDP site, and conflict- and flood-affected counties across the country.</narrative>
  </description>
